(20, 'spectacle', 'six-pm', 'SIX P.M.', 'Creative Design House Co., Ltd.', '449/6 Soi Sawaisuwan, Bangsue, Bangkok, 10800 THAILAND', '+668 9411 2780', 'cdh.co.th@gmail.com', '+66 2911 5959', 'www.sixpmthailand.com', 'www.facebook.com/sixpmthailand', 'https://www.instagram.com/sixpmthailand', '@sixpmthailand', 'https://drive.google.com/open?id=1nBwQe4e-8rhNk497gcWzqD_9sSBWU_TK', 'SS19 - No Connection', 'EH 100 : Y - 04', 'SIX P.M. was founded in Bangkok in 2011 by the founder and Creative Director, Chanchai Suwannachaya(10 Finalist of Vogue Who’s on Next Thailand 2014), to served an alternative style of fashion. The core is to make a luxury and high quality unique streetwear for young professional with creative mindset. The brand\'s ethos came from the analysis of a metropolitan\'s lifestyle, full of stress, competitive but, eager to success. This personally meanwhile needs to keep their inherent identity differed from others. The keyword is to break the rule of perfection by intention to create garments not too perfect. Imperfection beneath the perfection became our brand signature, luxury but disobedience, to offers a balance between a look of creative and luxury.\n\nSIX P.M. creates outfits with sense of creative french style, offering modern look through subtle and oversized silhouette, creative techniques and imperfect details.  The brand launched to serve for young blood professional market, targeting fashion innovators and early fashion adopters who live their life with SIX P.M. as a tool of fashion. SIX P.M. Spring/Summer 2019 collection was inspired by the theme, “How to live without the internet.” In our current society, everything is connected to the internet and technology is advancing faster than ever. Social media is menacing our everyday life slowly, as people can’t live without scrolling through their homepage on Instagram or Facebook. Thus, the presence of social network is replacing real-life interactions and everything is becoming an online illusion. \n\nThis season, the designer’s intention is to reflect our actions, use minimal amount of internet and start interacting with people around you. “No Connection” Spring/Summer ’19 is launching soon. Are you ready for it?\n\nThe colour range is extracted from digital colour tones like Digital green, Bright blue and Highlight yellow. The graphics used are to portray the anti-online movement with a message, “stop using too much internet.” Most pieces have projected an androgynous vibe, which its silhouettes are reworked and irregular. The final touches of each apparel uphold SIX P.M. identity as intricate details like unfinished seams, raw trims, unique paper patterns and imperfect finishing, are always our brand’s signature. ', 'SIX P.M. Spring/Summer 2019 collection was inspired by the theme, “How to live without the internet.” In our current society, everything is connected to the internet and technology is advancing faster than ever. Social media is menacing our everyday life slowly, as people can’t live without scrolling through their homepage on Instagram or Facebook. Thus, the presence of social network is replacing real-life interactions and everything is becoming an online illusion. ', 1, '2018-10-13 13:09:30', NULL),
